# Inlines

This is an inline ![image of palm trees](palm-trees.jpg) image with alt text.  
The alt text forces this image to be displayed as a figure. Thus, the figure
gets its own line and caption.


This ![](palm-trees.jpg) is an inline image without a caption.  


# Full bleed image

{fullbleed: true}
![](palm-trees.jpg)


# Full bleed image With Caption

{fullbleed: true}
![This is alt text](palm-trees.jpg)

# Image with width of 150%

{width: 150%}
![](palm-trees.jpg)

You can see that despite the 150% width, the image is not displayed larger than the margins allow.

# Left aligned image with a width of 150%

{width: 150%, align: left}
![](palm-trees.jpg)

# Right aligned image with a width of 150%

{width: 150%, align: right}
![](palm-trees.jpg)

